snippet.title: Happy Birthday Mother Teresa!
snippet.description:
An epitome of humanity and a personification of unconditional love! Mother Teresa led the world by example, living a life for others. Her joy in serving those in need knew no bounds and her compassion will be remembered forever.

#mothertheresaday #love #selflessness #selflesslove #motherteresa #stteresaofcalcutta

snippet.title: Leave Me Alone | Save The Tiger
snippet.description:
We glorify tigers in pop culture, be it the protective Rajah in Aladdin or the cute Tigger in Winnie The Pooh. In reality, we have constantly been at war with them. To raise awareness about tiger conservation, 29th July of every year is observed as International Tigers’ Day. Here are a few facts about tigers that might surprise you!

#internationaltigersday #tiger #tigers #nature #environment #conservation #wildlife #nationalanimal #rajah #aladdin #tigger #winniethepooh #savethetiger

snippet.title: The future tallest building will be taller than 3 Burj Khalifa's put together! 😱
snippet.description:
It’s the Skyscraper Day! The day is observed on the birth anniversary of the American architect, Louis H. Sullivan, the father of modern skyscrapers. Let’s take a quick look at the popular skyscrapers in the world and some that are coming up in the future!

snippet.title: It is time to say Checkmate!
snippet.description:
Chess requires strategic thinking and high levels of concentration. But most importantly, it requires patience - by which we mean hundreds of hours of waiting! Happy International Chess Day to all the chess lovers!

#internationalchessday #chess #chessgame #chesslover #game #patience #concentration

snippet.title: World Asteroid Day
snippet.description:
The United Nations observes World Asteroid Day to educate people about asteroids. It was co-founded by Stephen Hawking and a host of over 200 astronauts, scientists, technologists and artists.
